PrecisAppointment of MARK GLAUSER as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Federated States of Micronesia, with residence in Canberra; JAMAL KHOKHAR as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Azerbaijan, with residence in Ankara; FRANÇOIS LAFRENIÈRE as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of the Union of Myanmar; CAMERON MACKAY as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Indonesia; CAROL MCQUEEN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Benin, with residence in Ouagadougou; DAVID MURPHY as Consul General of Canada in Shanghai (People's Republic of China); PHILIPPE RHEAULT as Consul General of Canada in Guangzhou (People’s Republic of China); ULRIC SHANNON as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Iraq; and CHRISTOPHER WILKIE as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the People’s Democratic Republic of Algeria.
